<br>
The original list is very close to being ordered by delay assuming EB/TB &gt; misc hate generating effects<br>
<br>
Blade of War Delay: 32<br>
Obsidian Greatblade Delay: 35<br>
Aggression Delay: 40<br>
Stone Etched War Sword Delay: 30 <br>
Bloodied Berserker's Blade Delay: 40 <br>
Gaudralek, Sword of the Sky Delay: 38 <br>
Norge`tal Delay: 45<br>
<br>
Hate generated by proc clustering assuming EB &gt; Rune III &gt; TB &gt; misc hate generating effects<br>
<br>
Blade of War - EB<br>
Obsidian Greatblade - EB<br>
Stone Etched War Sword - Rune III <br>
Bloodied Berserker's Blade - Rune III <br>
Aggression - TB<br>
Gaudralek, Sword of the Sky - misc<br>
Norge`tal - misc<br>
<br>
Assuming that a &gt; 10% delay reduction is sufficient to &quot;promote&quot; a weapon in the order<br>
<br>
Blade of War Delay: 32<br>
Stone Etched War Sword Delay: 30 <br>
Obsidian Greatblade Delay: 35<br>
Bloodied Berserker's Blade Delay: 40 <br>
Aggression Delay: 40<br>
Gaudralek, Sword of the Sky Delay: 38 <br>
Norge`tal Delay: 45<br>
<br>
This look pretty close to what people are reporting with only &quot;nearest neighbor&quot; order debatable.<br>
<br>
Ranking the 1 handers is somewhat easier since with max haste they are all at minimum delay.<br>
<br>
Finally, to play the broken record once again -<br>
<br>
2 - 1 handers (EB/TB) will very likely secure aggro more quickly and hold it better than almost any 2 hander. For this reason, only the top three or four 2 handers are likely to be usable in all situations.<br>
<br>
2 - 1 handers will get you killed with most high damage reposting mobs. The alternative is a 2H aggro weapon or a shield.<br>
